cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with identifying inaccurate data in AI, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper proposes a new method based on qualitative correlations among related data, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories, as the paper deals with identifying inaccurate data in these fields. The paper also proposes a new concept called support coefficient function (SCF), which is relevant to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper presents an algorithm for interpreting infrared spectra, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
